goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of fertility vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any relationship between fertility and life expectancy. If there is a negative correlation, it means that countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancies and vice versa.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility across different countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of fertility rates across different countries. We can identify countries with high and low fertility rates and also the range of fertility rates.

goals.question: What is the difference between predicted and actual life expectancy?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the accuracy of the model used to predict life expectancy. We can identify countries where the model over-predicted or under-predicted life expectancy.

goals.question: What is the relationship between predicted and actual life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of p_life_expect vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the accuracy of the model used to predict life expectancy. If there is a strong positive correlation, it means that the model is accurate in predicting life expectancy.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across different countries?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['difference'] = data['p_life_expect'] - data['life_expect']
    data = data.sort_values(by='difference', ascending=False)
    
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='country', y='difference', legend=False)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the difference between predicted and actual life expectancy?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
